merchandiseItemRenderer.title: Screwdriver Black and Orange / Silver Shaft | Linus Tech Tips
merchandiseItemRenderer.description: "Big Screwdriver" Giveaway Promotion While supplies last, buyers of our "Screwdriver" located in North America may be selected to win a "Big Screwdriver" - similar to the one featured in this livestream on the Linus Tech Tips YouTube channel, valued at approximately $1,000 - OR the $2,200 gaming computer showcased in the same livestream, with the purchase of their screwdriver, based on random draw. Once entries close, our team will select two winners - one for each prize - from all eligible entries. Odds of winning vary depending on the number of submissions. There is 1 of each prize available in total. Once these items have been given away, they will not be restocked or made available again for this promotion. No purchase necessary. 1 free entry per person is available by mail to our distribution center. Address:MIBC Distribution ATTN: Big Screwdriver Giveaway11411 Blacksmith Pl unit#6Richmond, BC V7A 4T7Canada Exclusions: customers & free entries from Quebec are not eligible for this promotion. Submissions based on eligible purchase end May 24, 2024 at 11:59:59pm Pacific time. No purchase necessary submissions will only be accepted if postmarked on or before May 27, 2024. Draw will occur June 10, 2024, and the eligible winner will be contacted by email. Our ratcheting multi-bit screwdriver features a knurled stainless steel shaft with a strong embedded magnet, internal storage for 12 "shorty" 20mm bits (or 6 full-sized bits), an in-house designed three-lobe handle for comfort and ergonomics, and a tastefully-embossed LTT logo on the end cap. The ratchet is based on Megapro's long-standing & reliable design, but has been significantly modified to suit our needs. We reversed the ratchet direction (right for clockwise, left for anti-clockwise), adjusted the spring for lighter back-force which allows you to ratchet-drive even very small screws, and optimized for smoothness and quiet function. It's rated for operation of up to 220 inch-pounds of force. Our bit storage is another collaboration with Megapro. We utilized their patented bit clip storage design, but adjusted the length of the clips & the size of the total cavity to allow for our smaller, more ergonomic handle. All external plastics are Triax 1120 - a Nylon and ABS polymer which is great for injection molding parts like ours - for its overall durability and chemical resistance. The only exception is the black "accent ring" on the all black versions, which are made from machined Delrin, and the orange "accent ring" on the black & orange version, which are made from injection molded ABS. Internal plastics in our ratchet are also made from Delrin for its self-lubricating properties, and our ratchet housing is made from Zinc. Our industrial-looking black phosphate-coated S2 steel bits are durable and rust resistant. Standard bit set included with the screwdriver: PH0, PH1, PH2, H2, H2.5, H4, SL2, SL4, SL6, SQ1, SQ2, and our 5x5 Magnet bit (affectionately named "The Screw Retriever") (This was previously listed as a 6x6 magnet bit, but that was incorrect. The size is 5x5mm) NOTE: Bits are a consumable item and will wear or break down over time. Visual wear to the black phosphate coating is normal and expected. Other bit sets are available for purchase at https://www.lttstore.com/products/bits Using patents from Megapro Tools Inc.: 5,265,504 & 7,258,046 WARNING: Not compliant with airport security restrictions in some countries (including but not limited to US and Canada). Verify all security/travel restrictions before traveling with your screwdriver!

merchandiseItemRenderer.title: Backpack | Linus Tech Tips
merchandiseItemRenderer.description: The definitive version of the LTT Backpack is now available! Featuring our updated Titanium Carabiner zipper pulls, as well as a bonded dual-layer bottom panel, this bag is purpose-built to keep your tech and accessories safe and secure. New orders placed on or after April 29 are expected to ship by July 31, 2024. We thoughtfully designed the 22 pockets & sleeves for a wide variety of daily uses. This bag can accommodate multiple laptops or tablets, portable game consoles, accessories, and hardware/tools - including a pocket dedicated to the LTT Screwdriver, and a hidden Airtag sleeve near the water bottle sleeve in our vast main storage pocket (we've affectionately called this one the "bag of holding" internally).All straps & stitches have been reinforced well beyond what an average user would need, including our triple-rivet-reinforced top handle which can hold up to a pull force of 778.6N (175lb or 79kg).We've aimed for the best possible materials in all aspects. Our main material is a Repreve Polyester with a water-resistant lining which we tested to an AATCC water repellency rating of 80 (spills & light rain will bead on its surface), and - like other materials from Repreve - is made entirely from recycled plastic water bottles. Our zippers are, of course, from the legendary YKK - they're water-resistant across all external pockets & sport standard YKK zipper pulls on all zippered pockets. This bag's internal carrying capacity is 25.5L, and the external volume is 35L. That big difference is primarily due to the abundance of padding & reinforcement throughout the bag, including between pockets & below the laptop sleeve, ensuring that your devices should never slide directly onto a hard surface when inserted into a sleeve. Max laptop size for largest sleeve: 11.25 x 15.5 x 1.25" (28.575 x 39.37 x 3.175cm) Meets carry-on standards for most airlines (just barely fits under the seat!) For more info about the bag, check out the variety of photos down below! Note: There is a known issue that may cause previously sold backpacks' zipper pulls to be more fragile than intended. For information, see here. New orders from Oct 27, 2023 are shipped with standard zipper pulls in place of the previous carabiner option.

merchandiseItemRenderer.title: Tech Sack | Linus Tech Tips
merchandiseItemRenderer.description: The perfect accessory for the LTT Backpack, and for travelers of all types. Utilizing the same water resistant fabric found on the LTT Backpack, our Tech Sack is meant to keep your small items organized in transit, whether those are cables, tools, toiletries, or cosmetics. It includes 8 internal sleeves for tech or other small items to keep things organized and separated, as well as water resistant YKK zippers to ensure a quality seal and feel. And for good measure, we included elastic loops for cables, pens, tools or any other items that you want to transport securely, as well as a hidden interior zipper pocket for items that can't be misplaced. The reinforced webbing handle provides an easy grip if stored in bags of any size, and provides an easy anchor point if you prefer to attach it to the outside of your bag with a carabiner. This is the ideal small bag for everyday carry, traveling, and general organization.

merchandiseItemRenderer.title: 3D Down Jacket XX-Large | Linus Tech Tips
merchandiseItemRenderer.description: Lightweight, breathable, AND insulating?? The LTT 3D Down Jacket has it all. The cornerstone feature is an 11-layer fabric which features goose down fibers in the middle layer. The down is included to provide its classic, fantastic heat insulation. The 3D printing machines used in the creation of this fabric arrange the down fibers in a "cobweb" pattern, which allows room between the fibers for increased airflow and breathability. The process of creating this fabric is a bit different than what you'd find in a standard extrusion-based plastic printer, but it shares some of the underlying principles as an additive process which "deposits" the fibers rather than weaving them. Utilizing a blend of nylon and spandex, the outer layer of the jacket provides enough stretch to remain comfortable in active use, as well as some water resistance in rain or snow (greater than 1800mm water resistance in our testing). And of course, no LTT garment would be complete without YKK zippers, as well as an array of pockets - 3 exterior zippered pockets, 1 interior zippered pocket, and 1 interior sleeve pocket. To top it all off, we added a beaded heat transfer print with an LTT logo on the right hip, as well as a small printed strip under the rear neck.
